-- FTSE 350 pension deficit steady at 89 bln stg in September -Mercer
-- By Simon Jessop
-- Thu Oct 02, 2014 12:07PM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Oct 2 (Reuters) - The 350 biggest UK-listed companies had a combined defined benefit pension deficit of 89 billion pounds ($143.59 billion) at the end of September, from 90 billion pounds in August, consultants Mercer said.

